I think swap will swap the data, but I think we want the rhs side objects data to be invalidated. For cases such as these. 

 vector<int> func() {
    ....
    return vec;
}

x = func();

This is where we want the move constructor to work instead of the copy constructor, thus x will get all the data of the return value, but the return value should be invalidated and not take on the value of x, Thus what was inside x is not freed and that may cause memory leakage.

